name: FW/PBS, Inc. v. City of Dallas
Lewis v. Jeffers
question:
Can a federal district court conduct an independent review of the evidence of a state court’s finding of a constitutional aggravating circumstance?

Did Arizona’s construction of the “especially heinous…or depraved” aggravating circumstance contravene Supreme Court precedent?
description: A case in which the Court held that federal habeas corpus relief is not intended to find error in state laws but rather to determine whether a state court’s finding was so arbitrary and capricious that it violates the Eighth Amendment.

name: United States v. Eichman
question: Did the Act violate freedom of expression protected by the First Amendment?
description: A case in which the Court held that a federal law criminalizing the burning of an American flag violated the freedom of expression guaranteed by the First Amendment.

name: Baltimore City Department of Social Services v. Bouknight
Illinois v. Rodriguez
question:
(1) Is a police officer's good faith reliance on a third party's apparent authority to consent to a search a valid exception to the warrant requirement of the Fourth Amendment?

(2) Did the woman possess actual authority to permit a consensual entry?

name: Jimmy Swaggart Ministries v. Board of Equalization of California
question: Did California's imposition of a sales and use tax on the sale of religious materials violate the Free Exercise or Establishment Clauses of the First Amendment?

name: Pension Benefit Guaranty Corporation v. LTV Corporation
Board of Education of Westside Community Schools v. Mergens By and Through Mergens
question: Was Westside's prohibition against the formation of a Christian club consistent with the Establishment Clause, thereby rendering the Equal Access Act unconstitutional?
description: A case in which the Court held that the Equal Access Act stopped Westside High School from prohibiting the formation of religious-based non-curricular student clubs.

name: Franchise Tax Board of California v. Alcan Aluminium, Limited
Guidry v. Sheet Metal Workers National Pension Fund
Pennsylvania v. Muniz
question: Do incriminating utterances of a drunk-driving suspect constitute self-incrimination under the Fifth Amendment?
description: A case in which the Court held that the Fifth Amendment distinguishes between real or physical evidence and testimonial evidence, of which only testimonial evidence is protected under the Amendment.

name: California v. Federal Energy Regulatory Commission
Michigan Citizens for Independent Press v. Thornburgh
Illinois v. Perkins
question: Did the undercover police officer violate the accused's Miranda rights as protected by the Fifth and Fourteenth Amendments?

name: Rutan v. Republican Party of Illinois
question: Did Governor Thompson's practices in Illinois infringe upon the First Amendment rights of potential and current state employees?

name: W.S. Kirkpatrick & Company, Inc. v. Environmental Tectonics Corporation, International
question: Does state doctrine prohibit a US court from adjudicating a case that would attribute unlawful acts to foreign officials acting in their official capacity?
description: A case in which the Court held that state doctrine only applies when the case requires a US court to declare an act of a foreign sovereign nation invalid.

name: Chauffeurs, Teamsters and Helpers Local No. 391 v. Terry
Florida v. Wells
question: Does the Fourth Amendment allow the police to open closed containers during an inventory search where the suspect gave permission to open the truck where the container was found?
description: A case in which the Court held that the Fourth Amendment does not allow the police to open closed containers during an inventory search where the suspect gave permission to open the truck where the container was found.

name: Peel v. Attorney Registration and Disciplinary Commission of Illinois
question: Does listing National Board of Trial Advocacy certifications on an attorney's letterhead have the potential to mislead the public to an extent that warrants a categorical ban of that type of advertising?

name: Portland Golf Club v. Commissioner of Internal Revenue
United States Department of Labor v. Triplett
Eli Lilly and Company v. Medtronic, Inc.
question: Are activities that would normally constitute patent infringement excused if they are used to develop and submit information to the Food and Drug Administration to obtain marketing approval for a medical device?
description: A case in which the Court decided whether activities that would normally constitute patent infringement are excused if they are used to develop and submit information to the Food and Drug Administration to obtain marketing approval for a medical device.

name: Port Authority Trans-Hudson Corporation v. Feeney
Sisson v. Ruby
question: Does a federal district court have jurisdiction over a suit to limit the liability of a yacht owner regarding the fire on his vessel?
description: A case in which the Court held that the district court has maritime jurisdiction when the incident in question represents a potential hazard to maritime commerce and bears a substantial relationship to maritime activity.

name: Burnham v. Superior Court of California, County of Marin
question: Does the Due Process Clause of the Fourteenth Amendment prohibit state courts from exercising jurisdiction over a nonresident who was temporarily in the state and was personally served with process in a suit unrelated to his presence in the state?
description: A case in which the Court held that states have jurisdiction over nonresidents within their borders.

name: Dole v. United Steelworkers of America
Austin v. Michigan Chamber of Commerce
question: Did the Michigan Campaign Finance Act violate the First and Fourteenth Amendments?

name: Pennsylvania Department of Public Welfare v. Davenport
Idaho v. Wright
question: Does the admission at trial of hearsay testimony made by a child to an examining pediatrician violate the Confrontation Clause of the Sixth Amendment?
description: A case in which the Court held that hearsay testimony made by a child to an examining pediatrician admitted at trial violates the Confrontation Clause of the Sixth Amendment.

name: Ohio v. Akron Center for Reproductive Health
question: Do the judicial bypass requirements, the physician notification element, and the burden of proof mandated by the parental notification bill violate a minor’s Fourteenth Amendment due process rights?
description: A case in which the Court held that an Ohio bill requiring physicians to notify the parents of an unmarried minor who is requesting an abortion did not violate a minor’s right to due process under the Fourteenth Amendment.

name: Adams Fruit Company, Inc. v. Barrett
Federal Trade Commission v. Superior Court Trial Lawyers Association
Employment Division, Department of Human Resources of Oregon v. Smith
question: Can a state deny unemployment benefits to a worker fired for using illegal drugs for religious purposes?
description: A case in which the Court held that the First Amendment does not protect individuals engaging in illegal acts as part of a religious ceremony.

name: United States v. Montalvo-Murillo
question: Did the district court err in holding that the defendant must be released as a remedy for the government’s failure to hold a timely detention hearing?
description: A case in which the Court held that the district court erred in holding that the defendant must be released as a remedy for the government’s failure to hold a timely detention hearing.

name: Alabama v. White
question: Does an anonymous tip alone provide a reasonable suspicion sufficent to stop and search an individual’s car?

name: Howlett By and Through Howlett v. Rose
Lujan v. National Wildlife Federation
question: Does an organization representing private citizens who use public land "in the vicinity" of areas affected by Bureau of Land Management (BLM) land-use designations have standing to challenge those designations under section 10(e) of the Administrative Procedure Act? Does standing to challenge several individual BLM decision confer standing to challenge those decisions as a whole, even when the organization's members are not affected by the bulk of the decisions?

name: Metro Broadcasting, Inc. v. Federal Communications Commission
question: Did the FCC's minority preference policies violate the equal protection component of the Fifth Amendment?

name: National Labor Relations Board v. Curtin Matheson Scientific, Inc.
Keller v. State Bar of California
Missouri v. Jenkins
question: Did the court order to increase property taxes violate Article III, the Tenth Amendment, or principles of federal/state comity?

name: Chesapeake and Ohio Railway Company v. Schwalb
Walton v. Arizona
question: Are the Arizona state statutes governing death penalty sentencing constitutional under the Sixth Amendment?
description: A case in which the Court held that the Arizona method of death penalty sentencing is not arbitrary and does not place an undue burden on the defendant.

name: Pavelic & LeFlore v. Marvel Entertainment Group, A Division of Cadence Industries Corporation
United States v. Goodyear Tire and Rubber Company
United Steelworkers of America, AFL-CIO-CLC v. Rawson
Maryland v. Craig
question: Did the closed-circuit testimony violate the Confrontation Clause of the Sixth Amendment?

name: John Doe Agency v. John Doe Corporation
Horton v. California
question: Does the Fourth Amendment prohibit the warrantless seizure of evidence in plain sight if the discovery of such evidence was not inadvertent?

name: United States v. Energy Resources Company, Inc.
Georgia v. South Carolina
question: What is the proper boundary between Georgia and South Carolina?

name: Office of Personnel Management v. Richmond
question: Does receipt of erroneous information from a government employee entitle a claimant to benefits he would not otherwise receive?

name: Yellow Freight System, Inc. v. Donnelly
United States v. Verdugo-Urquidez
question: Does the Fourth Amendment apply to the search and seizure by United States agents of property that is owned by a nonresident alien and located in a foreign country?

name: Breininger v. Sheet Metal Workers International Association Local Union No. 6
Wilder v. Virginia Hospital Association
question: Did the Boren Amendment create a "right" under the definition of 42 U.S.C. 1983, therefore allowing private parties to bring suit challenging the state's finding that its Medicaid reimbursement rates are "reasonable and adequate"? If such a right was created, did Congress intend to prevent private suits to enforce the it?

name: Kaiser Aluminum & Chemical Corporation v. Bonjorno
Northbrook National Insurance Company v. Brewer
Grady v. Corbin
question: Does the Double Jeopardy Clause of the Fifth Amendment prevent a person from being charged with more severe offenses after being tried and convicted of lesser ones for the same action?

name: Atlantic Richfield Company v. USA Petroleum Company
question: Must a competitor alleging an "antitrust injury" under the Clayton Act prove predatory intent in addition to showing that the defendant conspired to fix prices in violation of the Sherman Act?

name: Metro Broadcasting, Inc. v. Federal Communications Commission
question: Does the FCC's minority preference policy, giving preference to minority ownership bids for new radio or television broadcasting licenses and permitting "distress sales" to minority owned enterprises only, violate a nonminority bidder's' Fifth Amendment equal protection rights?

name: Commissioner, Immigration and Naturalization Service v. Jean
Osborne v. Ohio
question: Did Ohio's ban on the possession of child pornography violate the First Amendment?

name: General Motors Corporation v. United States
Maryland v. Buie
question: Does the Fourth Amendment prevent police officers from making a “protective sweep” at the site of an in-home arrest if they do not believe themselves or others to be in immediate danger?

name: United States v. Kokinda
question: Is a sidewalk that is entirely contained by Postal Service property and intended only for traffic to and from Postal Service buildings a public forum? If it is a public forum, does a prohibition of solicitation pass strict scrutiny? If it is not a public forum, does it pass a "reasonableness" test?

name: Golden State Transit Corporation v. City of Los Angeles
Commissioner of Internal Revenue v. Indianapolis Power & Light Company
Michigan Department of State Police v. Sitz
question: Did the drunk driving checkpoints violate motorists' privacy protected by the Fourth Amendment?

name: Fort Stewart Schools v. Federal Labor Relations Authority
Milkovich v. Lorain Journal Company
question: Are the statements in the newspaper article constitutionally protected opinions?

name: Department of Treasury, Internal Revenue Service v. Federal Labor Relations Authority
Maislin Industries, US, Inc. v. Primary Steel, Inc.
University of Pennsylvania v. Equal Employment Opportunity Commission
question: Does requiring a university to disclose confidential peer review materials in an investigation violate the First Amendment?

name: New York v. Harris
question: Is the statement of a defendant inadmissible if it is the result of the police entering the defendant’s home without a warrant or consent in violation of the Fourth Amendment?

name: Cruzan by Cruzan v. Director, Missouri Department of Health
question: Did the Due Process Clause of the Fourteenth Amendment permit Cruzan's parents to refuse life-sustaining treatment on their daughter's behalf?
description: A case in which the Court held that a Missouri state hospital had the right to keep a patient in a vegetative state alive, despite the wishes of the patient's parents, due to a lack of otherwise "clear and convincing" wishes on the part of the patient.

name: Hodgson v. Minnesota
question: Did the Minnesota abortion notification statute unconstitutionally restrict a minor's access to having an abortion?

name: James v. Illinois
question: Could James's statements be used against him even though they were obtained illegally?

name: Citibank, N.A. v. Wells Fargo Asia Ltd.
